{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"linear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"duration","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@NSTimeInterval","text":"TimeInterval","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore9AnimationV","text":"Animation","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Animation"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"parameters":[{"name":"duration","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The length of time, expressed in seconds, that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the animation takes to complete.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"return-value","text":"Return Value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A linear animation with a specified duration.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A linear animation provides a mechanical feel to the motion because its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"speed is consistent from start to finish of the animation. This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"constant speed makes a linear animation ideal for animating the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"movement of objects where changes in the speed might feel awkward, such","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as with an activity indicator.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"code":"linear(duration:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" when you want to specify the time it takes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for the animation to complete. Otherwise, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Animation\/linear"},{"text":" to perform the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"animation for a default length of time.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The following code shows an example of using linear animation with a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"duration of two seconds to animate the movement of a circle as it moves","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"between the leading and trailing edges of the view. The color of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"circle also animates from red to blue as it moves across the view.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct ContentView: View {","    @State private var isActive = false","","    var body: some View {","        VStack(alignment: isActive ? .trailing : .leading) {","            Circle()","                .fill(isActive ? Color.red : Color.blue)","                .frame(width: 50, height: 50)","","            Button(\"Animate\") {","                withAnimation(.linear(duration: 2.0)) {","                    isActive.toggle()","                }","            }","            .frame(maxWidth: .infinity)","        }","    }","}"]}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Animation\/linear(duration:)"},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"linear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"duration","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@NSTimeInterval","text":"TimeInterval","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdenti